<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idp84325552">
<term>cathodic protection</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm129596736">method of protecting metal by using a sacrificial anode and effectively making the metal that needs protecting the cathode, thus preventing its oxidation</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm126591232">
<term>corrosion</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm141404192">degradation of metal through an electrochemical process</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm145050816">
<term>galvanized iron</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm145020128">method for protecting iron by covering it with zinc, which will oxidize before the iron; zinc-plated iron</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm153016624">
<term>sacrificial anode</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm87614912">more active, inexpensive metal used as the anode in cathodic protection; frequently made from magnesium or zinc</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
